{
  "texts": [
    "Regarding the techniques, in-context learning leads to more contextualized and appropriate responses in ODDs, while fine-tuning improves contextualization and appropriateness in TODs.",
    "Regarding the base LLMs, in KGDs adapting Llama2 C with in-context learning leads to the best results, while Mistral I benefits the most from fine-tuning.",
    "Furthermore, in QA the quality of knowledge impacts contextualization and validity the most, while adaptation techniques have a minor effect.",
    "To better understand the shortcomings of the techniques, we investigate the motivations provided by the annotators to support their negative judgments.",
    "For each technique, we considered the scenario with gold external knowledge as the theoretical upper bound (except for ODDs where no external knowledge is required)."
  ]
}